---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="The Future of AI in Web Development | Balaji Blogs" description="Exploring how artificial intelligence is transforming the way we build, design, and interact with websites in the modern era.">
  <article class="animate-in">
    <header class="article-header">
      <h1>The Future of AI in Web Development</h1>
      <div class="article-meta">Published on April 20, 2026 &bull; 5 min read</div>
    </header>

    <div class="article-content">
      <p>Artificial intelligence is no longer just a buzzword; it's practically rewriting the rules of web development. From intelligent code completion tools to automated debugging, AI assistants are streamlining workflows at an unprecedented rate.</p>

      <h2>Intelligent Design Systems</h2>
      <p>One of the most fascinating advancements is how AI integrates with design. Rather than manually crafting every responsive breakpoint, new systems can dynamically analyze content density and screen real estate to generate optimal layouts on the fly. This brings us closer to a "design once, adapt everywhere" paradigm.</p>

      <h2>Automated Testing</h2>
      <p>Quality assurance is another area experiencing a revolution. AI models can simulate thousands of user interactions, learning to spot edge-case bugs that human testers might miss. As these models evolve, they drastically reduce the time needed for deployment cycles.</p>

      <p>Ultimately, AI won't replace web developers. Instead, it will empower them to focus on architecture, creativity, and user experience, handling the repetitive boilerplate code reliably.</p>
    </div>

    <a href="/blog" class="back-link">&larr; Back to all articles</a>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .article-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .article-header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .article-meta {
    color: var(--muted-text);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .article-content {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 3rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--muted-text);
  }

  .article-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .article-content h2 {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-color);
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    color: var(--muted-text);
    transition: color 0.3s ease;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--accent-color);
  }
</style>
